                      <p class="style82">                      <strong>Data and methodological convergence: </em></strong></strong>What are genes other than data recorded on a different medium, and (also) what better way to study them than with computers? With the increasing sophistication of biomedical knowledge has come not only greater dependence on information technology analytical tools, but also the adoption of consortium techniques, standards and open source to further that knowledge. In the first piece below, NIST reports on an upcoming meeting to explore the formation of a consortium to study gene expression, while the second reports on the use of a dialect of the ever versatile XML (in this case, &ldquo;Systems Biology Markup Language&rdquo;, or SBML) to create an open source, online database to study biological models.</em> </em></strong></em></em></em></p></td>
